---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout>
  <!-- Background Mesh Gradient -->
  <div class="mesh-gradient-bg"></div>

  <!-- Hero Section -->
  <section class="relative overflow-hidden py-24 sm:py-32">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-7xl px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 text-center">
      <!-- Announcement Banner -->
      <div class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 rounded-full border border-hairline bg-canvas px-4 py-1 text-xs text-body shadow-vercel-sm mb-8">
        <span class="font-mono text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-wider text-link">New</span>
        <span class="h-3 w-px bg-hairline"></span>
        <span>Version 2.0 with PDF export & QR sharing.</span>
      </div>

      <!-- Tagline -->
      <h1 class="text-4xl font-semibold tracking-[-2.4px] text-ink sm:text-6xl max-w-3xl mx-auto leading-none">
        Split expenses. No accounts. Instant settlement.
      </h1>
      
      <!-- Subcopy -->
      <p class="mt-6 text-lg sm:text-xl text-body max-w-2xl mx-auto leading-relaxed">
        A Vercel-inspired bill splitter designed for developers, roommates, and travelers. 
        Zero logins, 100% client-side, offline-first. Split travel costs or subscription fees in seconds.
      </p>

      <!-- CTA Cluster -->
      <div class="mt-10 flex flex-col sm:flex-row items-center justify-center gap-4">
        <a 
          href="/app" 
          class="w-full sm:w-auto inline-flex h-12 items-center justify-center rounded-full bg-primary px-8 text-base font-semibold text-on-primary hover:bg-primary/95 transition-colors shadow-vercel-md"
        >
          Start Splitting Free
        </a>
        <a 
          href="#features" 
          class="w-full sm:w-auto inline-flex h-12 items-center justify-center rounded-full border border-hairline bg-canvas px-8 text-base font-semibold text-ink hover:bg-canvas-soft-2 transition-colors shadow-vercel-sm"
        >
          Learn More
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Feature Grid Section -->
  <section id="features" class="border-t border-hairline bg-canvas py-24 sm:py-32">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-7xl px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <div class="text-center max-w-3xl mx-auto">
        <p class="font-mono text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-wider text-mute">Built for Developers & Power Users</p>
        <h2 class="mt-2 text-3xl font-semibold tracking-[-1.28px] text-ink sm:text-4xl">
          Everything you need. Done locally.
        </h2>
        <p class="mt-4 text-base text-body">
          We stripped away the database, the signup forms, and the latency. You get pure utility.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="mt-16 grid grid-cols-1 gap-6 sm:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3">
        <!-- Feature 1 -->
        <div class="rounded-lg border border-hairline bg-canvas-soft p-6 shadow-vercel-sm transition-transform hover:-translate-y-0.5">
          <div class="font-mono text-xs text-mute mb-4">01 / SPEED</div>
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold tracking-tight text-ink">No Accounts Required</h3>
          <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-body">
            Skip the sign-up flow. Start splitting bills instantly the second you open the app.
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- Feature 2 -->
        <div class="rounded-lg border border-hairline bg-canvas-soft p-6 shadow-vercel-sm transition-transform hover:-translate-y-0.5">
          <div class="font-mono text-xs text-mute mb-4">02 / PRIVACY</div>
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold tracking-tight text-ink">100% Client-Side</h3>
          <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-body">
            All data is saved in your local browser storage. No servers, no tracking, completely secure.
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- Feature 3 -->
        <div class="rounded-lg border border-hairline bg-canvas-soft p-6 shadow-vercel-sm transition-transform hover:-translate-y-0.5">
          <div class="font-mono text-xs text-mute mb-4">03 / COLLABORATION</div>
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold tracking-tight text-ink">URL State Sharing</h3>
          <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-body">
            Encode your split state inside a compressed URL param. Just copy the link and send it.
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- Feature 4 -->
        <div class="rounded-lg border border-hairline bg-canvas-soft p-6 shadow-vercel-sm transition-transform hover:-translate-y-0.5">
          <div class="font-mono text-xs text-mute mb-4">04 / VERSATILITY</div>
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold tracking-tight text-ink">Dual Splitting Modes</h3>
          <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-body">
            Toggle between subscription mode for recurring costs or travel mode for group trips.
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- Feature 5 -->
        <div class="rounded-lg border border-hairline bg-canvas-soft p-6 shadow-vercel-sm transition-transform hover:-translate-y-0.5">
          <div class="font-mono text-xs text-mute mb-4">05 / MATHEMATICS</div>
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold tracking-tight text-ink">Smart Debt Minimization</h3>
          <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-body">
            Our settlement algorithm computes the minimum number of payments needed to clear all debts.
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- Feature 6 -->
        <div class="rounded-lg border border-hairline bg-canvas-soft p-6 shadow-vercel-sm transition-transform hover:-translate-y-0.5">
          <div class="font-mono text-xs text-mute mb-4">06 / EXPORT</div>
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold tracking-tight text-ink">PDFs & QR Codes</h3>
          <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-body">
            Export a high-quality PDF report or show a QR code for mobile scanning instantly.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- How It Works Section -->
  <section class="border-t border-hairline bg-canvas-soft py-24 sm:py-32">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-7xl px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <div class="text-center max-w-3xl mx-auto">
        <p class="font-mono text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-wider text-mute">Simple Workflow</p>
        <h2 class="mt-2 text-3xl font-semibold tracking-[-1.28px] text-ink sm:text-4xl">
          Three steps to settlement.
        </h2>
      </div>

      <div class="mt-16 grid grid-cols-1 gap-8 md:grid-cols-3 relative">
        <!-- Step 1 -->
        <div class="flex flex-col items-start p-6">
          <div class="flex h-8 w-8 items-center justify-center rounded-full bg-primary font-mono text-xs text-on-primary mb-6">1</div>
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-ink">Create Group & Add Members</h3>
          <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-body">
            Enter a group name, pick your currency, and add up to 30 members. No signup required.
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- Step 2 -->
        <div class="flex flex-col items-start p-6">
          <div class="flex h-8 w-8 items-center justify-center rounded-full bg-primary font-mono text-xs text-on-primary mb-6">2</div>
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-ink">Log Group Expenses</h3>
          <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-body">
            Add bills, titles, and amounts. Choose who paid and select which members split the expense.
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- Step 3 -->
        <div class="flex flex-col items-start p-6">
          <div class="flex h-8 w-8 items-center justify-center rounded-full bg-primary font-mono text-xs text-on-primary mb-6">3</div>
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-ink">Share & Settle Up</h3>
          <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-body">
            View the minimal payment matrix. Share the link, display the QR code, or export to PDF.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="mt-12 text-center">
        <a 
          href="/app" 
          class="inline-flex h-11 items-center justify-center rounded-full bg-primary px-6 text-sm font-semibold text-on-primary hover:bg-primary/95 transition-colors shadow-vercel-sm"
        >
          Try the App Now
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- FAQ Section -->
  <section class="border-t border-hairline bg-canvas py-24 sm:py-32">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-7xl px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl divide-y divide-hairline">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-semibold tracking-[-1.28px] text-ink text-center mb-12">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
        
        <!-- FAQ 1 -->
        <div class="py-6">
          <h3 class="text-base font-semibold text-ink font-sans">Where is my data stored?</h3>
          <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-body">
            All calculations and data exist entirely in your browser. We use local storage to save your groups. We do not use any databases or servers, keeping your financial activities private.
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- FAQ 2 -->
        <div class="py-6">
          <h3 class="text-base font-semibold text-ink font-sans">How does sharing work without a backend database?</h3>
          <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-body">
            We compress the entire group state (members, expenses, and config) into a short base64 string using `lz-string`. We append this string as a URL query parameter. When someone opens your shared link, the app extracts, decompresses, and loads it instantly.
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- FAQ 3 -->
        <div class="py-6">
          <h3 class="text-base font-semibold text-ink font-sans">Is SplitWhat really free?</h3>
          <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-body">
            Yes, it is 100% free. There are no premium tiers, no limits on number of groups, and absolutely no ads.
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- FAQ 4 -->
        <div class="py-6">
          <h3 class="text-base font-semibold text-ink font-sans">Can I use SplitWhat offline?</h3>
          <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-body">
            Yes. Since the app is built on Astro and uses 100% client-side logic for parsing, compiling, QR generating, and PDF printing, it runs perfectly without an active internet connection.
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- FAQ 5 -->
        <div class="py-6">
          <h3 class="text-base font-semibold text-ink font-sans">What happens if the sharing link gets too long?</h3>
          <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-body">
            Since the entire data is stored in the URL, a huge number of expenses will make the URL very long. We show a friendly warning if the URL exceeds 2,000 characters. To prevent this, keep your group lists under 300 expenses.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
